The paper deals with the problem of domain generalization in machine learning, specifically in the context of object recognition and medical image segmentation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a model-agnostic learning paradigm with gradient-based meta-train and meta-test procedures, which is a common approach in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also introduces two complementary losses which explicitly regularize the semantic structure of the feature space, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper demonstrates its effectiveness on object recognition benchmarks, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
